1. Exact Prompt Given to the AI

Write a Python 3 program that implements a simple Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) pipeline.

Requirements:
- Read a plain-text food delivery refund policy from Policy.txt.
- Split the text into fixed-size chunks.
- Generate embeddings using SentenceTransformer("all-MiniLM-L6-v2").
- Store embeddings in a FAISS index.
- Accept a user question.
- Retrieve the top 2 relevant chunks.
- Build and display a structured RAG prompt.
- Print a simulated answer.
- Continue until the user types "quit".

2. AI's Original Code and Corrected Version

AI Original Code: AI_Original.py

Corrected Version: improved_version.py

3. Changes Made

I tested the AI-generated code and found a few limitations. 
I improved the input handling by using strip() and lower() so the program accepts different forms of the quit command.
I also added validation for empty input and changed the retrieval logic using k = min(2, len(chunks)) to avoid errors when fewer than two chunks are available.
Finally, 
I improved the RAG prompt so that answers are generated only from the provided context, otherwise the response is "I don't know."